pageTitle: New Holland Offers New Edition of Popular Haymaker's Handbook | Hoards Dairyman
TableContextTimeStampBeforeTable: {6537=05.06.2011, 9018=In 1966, New Holland published the Haymaker’s Handbook, a practical “how-to” guidebook designed to help farmers and ranchers improve on hay and forage production. This booklet was so popular that it was revised and reprinted in 1987. Now a completely updated and revised Third Edition has been published and is available to a new generation of haymakers.}
